criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ASA (American Society of Anesthesiologist) grade II, full term singleton pregnancy
             subjects aged 18 to 50 years old;

          -  subjects undergoing elective cesarean section under combined spinal epidural
             anesthesia;

          -  volunteered to participate in the study and signed informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  related drug allergies or taboo;

          -  Severe cardiopulmonary disorders (New York Heart Association Classification III-IV, or
             left ventricular ejection fraction < 30%) and liver and kidney dysfunction (alanine
             aminotransferase exceeding the upper limit of normal value twice, creatinine exceeding
             the upper limit of normal value 1.5 times), alcoholism history;

          -  there are metabolic diseases such as gestational diabetes mellitus, or using drugs
             that affect metabolism;

          -  the subjects were unable to cooperate or to communicate;

          -  the subjects suffered from psychosocial diseases;

          -  participated in other clinical trials within one month;

          -  there is drug abuse.
